author: Danny Schwartz
title: First-Week Sales Projections For Migos' "CULTURE"
text:
Home > Music > First-Week Sales Projections For Migos'"CULTURE" First-Week Sales Projections For Migos'"CULTURE" 0 0 1 Posted by Danny Schwartz , Jan 30, 2017 at 10:02am Migos is in a duel for the #1 album in the country with country singer Brantley Gilbert. 
Migos scored its first #1 single (and first song to crack the top 50) in "Bad and Boujee." Now, they are locked in a battle for a #1 album. 
HDD has released first week sales projections for Migos' new album Culture. It is projected to sell 70-80K copies, including 28-33K in pure sales. HDD also projects country singer Brantley Gilbert's new album The Devil Donâ€™t Sleep to sell 70-80K copies, with 60-70K coming from pure sales. This one is going to be a nail-biter. 
Migos' 2015 debut album Yung Rich Nation sold 14 thousand copies its first week and debuted at #17 on the charts. The Atlanta trio has leveled up... stay tuned for final first-week sales results.
